The paper proposes an automatic model monitoring system for data streams that detects concept drift and generates alarm reports with explanations. This involves machine learning techniques such as unsupervised streaming algorithms and evaluation of results using human feedback from domain experts. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
